My Experience with Node.js & MongoDB:

I have 6 of hands-on experience with Node.js and MongoDB, working on multiple full-stack projects.
I have developed RESTful APIs, implemented authentication using JWT, and optimized database queries for performance.
Notable Projects:

I developed a full-stack Blog Application using the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js). This application allows users to create, read, update, and delete (CRUD) blog posts, ensuring a seamless and interactive user experience.

Key Features:
✅ User Authentication – Implemented secure JWT-based authentication for login/signup.
✅ Post Management – Users can create, edit, delete, and view their blog posts.
✅ Role-Based Access Control – Only post authors can edit or delete their posts.
✅ RESTful API – Designed a structured API using Express.js and MongoDB for efficient data handling.
✅ State Management – Used Redux Toolkit for managing global state and handling API requests efficiently.
✅ Optimized Performance – Implemented lazy loading, pagination, and caching techniques for a smooth experience.
✅ Frontend UI – Built with React.js and styled using Tailwind CSS.

Tech Stack:
Frontend: React.js, Redux Toolkit, React Router, Tailwind CSS
Backend: Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, Mongoose
Authentication: JWT (JSON Web Tokens)
Hosting: Deployed using Vercel (frontend) and Render (backend)
This project showcases my expertise in Node.js, MongoDB, API development, authentication, and database management, making me a strong fit for the Junior Backend Developer role at GuruCool Astro.

